FBIS3-14510 "drnes060_a_94007" FBIS-NES-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Mar 1994 ARAB AFRICA Algeria Retired Brigadier Named as Adviser to Head of State LD2603200394 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 GMT 26 Mar 94 LD2603200394 Algiers ENTV Television Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Mohamed Betchine has been appointed minister adviser to the head of state. Mohamed Betchine was born on 28 November 1934 in Constantine. He was a member of the National Liberation Army and a retired brigadier in the National Popular Army. He is a member of the National Council of Mujahidin. Betchine holds a diploma from the national school of artillery and the multi-weaponry high school in Russia. He pursued graduate research in law and occupied a number of positions in the National Popular Army until his retirement in August 1990. He is married and the father of six children.
